The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on April 30, 2019, designating May 2, 2019, as a National Day of Prayer in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of prayer in American history and society, emphasizing the nation's reliance on God's guidance and protection. It also reaffirms the commitment to religious freedom and condemns hate and violence in places of worship. The proclamation calls upon citizens to pray in accordance with their own faiths and express gratitude for the freedoms and blessings received.